00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,620
It has long been my privilege, dear listener, to accompany Sherlock Holmes through a series of

00:00:04,620 --> 00:00:09,120
adventures which have often placed us in the most curious and perplexing situations.

00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:13,220
Many of these episodes I have recorded in my journals, and on quiet evenings before the

00:00:13,220 --> 00:00:17,079
hearth at Baker Street, I have occasionally ventured to read them aloud to my companion,

00:00:17,079 --> 00:00:21,039
who though he feigned indifference, would sometimes offer a dry smile when some passage

00:00:21,039 --> 00:00:24,839
reminded him of the thrill of the chase or the satisfaction of a successful deduction.

00:00:24,839 --> 00:00:25,859
..

00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:29,080
The affair I now set down was one that drew much public notice in its day,

00:00:29,079 --> 00:00:32,230
involving as it did a member of the aristocracy,

00:00:32,230 --> 00:00:35,109
the sudden disappearance of a young American bride,

00:00:35,109 --> 00:00:37,280
you and vote, American bride,

00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:40,219
and the application of Holmes' singular reasoning powers

00:00:40,219 --> 00:00:43,329
to a case that baffled society and police alike.

00:00:43,329 --> 00:00:45,119
The newspapers gave it the title of

00:00:45,119 --> 00:00:47,049
The Adventure of the Noble Bachelor.

00:00:47,049 --> 00:00:49,420
To me, however, it remains first and foremost

00:00:49,420 --> 00:00:51,000
a story of Holmes' brilliance

00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,879
and of my own humble apprenticeship

00:00:52,879 --> 00:00:54,810
in the science of observation.

00:00:54,810 --> 00:00:57,459
The events began on a bleak October morning.

00:00:57,460 --> 00:01:00,719
A thin mist had spread itself over the grey roofs of London

00:01:00,719 --> 00:01:05,080
and the drizzle tapped drearily at the windows of our lodgings in Baker Street.

00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:08,960
Holmes was seated cross-legged upon the rug, dressing gown loose about him,

00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:12,129
his keen eyes fixed on the flames that curled in the grate.

00:01:12,129 --> 00:01:16,240
Before him, scattered upon the carpet, lay a number of freshly printed newspapers.

00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:20,240
I had only just returned from my early rounds and I found him in that absorbed attitude

00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:22,500
which betokened the presence of some problem.

00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:24,659
Hmm, Holmes, hmm.

00:01:24,659 --> 00:01:29,319
You seem as intent upon those pages as though they conceal the very secrets of the kingdom.

00:01:29,319 --> 00:01:32,259
What is it that holds your attention so closely?

00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:36,870
The kingdom, my dear Watson, may rest safely for the present.

00:01:36,870 --> 00:01:40,710
It is not treason I study, but matrimony.

00:01:40,710 --> 00:01:43,039
Matrimony! You astound me.

00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:46,879
I should not have suspected you of interest in so domestic a topic.

00:01:46,879 --> 00:01:51,879
Nor am I interested in the sentimental aspect, I assure you.

00:01:51,879 --> 00:01:58,620
My concern lies in the peculiar circumstances surrounding a union much discussed in society,

00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:05,619
circles these last days, that of Lord Robert Saints, Simon, the youngest son of the Duke

00:02:05,619 --> 00:02:12,129
of Balmoral, and a certain Miss Hattie Doran, daughter of a wealthy American.

00:02:12,129 --> 00:02:17,199
He drew one of the papers toward him and pointed to the announcement, where indeed the engagement

00:02:17,199 --> 00:02:19,639
had been chronicled with much flourish.

00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:25,430
Observe, Watson, a nobleman of ancient lineage, though without vast means,

00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:29,329
takes to wife a young lady of considerable fortune.

00:02:29,329 --> 00:02:35,930
Such alliances are common enough in our age, but the aftermath, ah, there lies the matter of interest.

00:02:35,930 --> 00:02:41,229
The bride has vanished, Watson. She disappeared upon her wedding morning.

00:02:41,229 --> 00:02:44,859
Vanished? Surely you do not mean she has been abducted?

00:02:44,860 --> 00:02:49,560
That is one possibility, though not the most probable.

00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:52,440
Here, read these accounts.

00:02:52,440 --> 00:03:14,860
.......................

00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:16,570
she had fled of her own accord,

00:03:16,570 --> 00:03:19,090
others that some misadventure had befallen her.

00:03:19,090 --> 00:03:20,960
The police were engaged upon the case,

00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,650
but as yet without result.

00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:24,760
This is certainly a singular occurrence.

00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:27,140
And Lord St. Simon, how does he bear the matter?

00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,890
According to the report,

00:03:28,890 --> 00:03:30,030
with dignity,

00:03:30,030 --> 00:03:33,020
though not without visible irritation,

00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:34,820
he has placed himself

00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:37,880
in communication with Scotland Yard

00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:41,509
and Lestrade has the conduct of the case.

00:03:41,509 --> 00:03:44,629
Then no doubt the mystery will soon be unraveled.

00:03:44,629 --> 00:03:58,420
my dear fellow lestrade is energetic but not always illuminating this affair requires delicate handling for there are undercurrents which the official mind does not readily perceive

00:03:58,419 --> 00:04:02,719
He paused, stretched out his long arm, and plucked another journal from the heap.

00:04:02,719 --> 00:04:04,659
His quick eyes ran down the columns.

00:04:04,659 --> 00:04:07,519
Ah, just as I surmised.

00:04:07,519 --> 00:04:13,659
The father, Mr. Francis Duran, is described as a man of rough speech,

00:04:13,659 --> 00:04:20,740
but of sterling qualities, a Californian, who amassed his fortune in the mines.

00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:26,620
The daughter, Hattie, is said to be high-spirited, with a certain independence of manner,

00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:29,759
which is scarcely surprising given her origin.

00:04:29,759 --> 00:04:31,250
Note this also.

00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:36,670
She was reported to have been attended by a former suitor, a certain mister.

00:04:36,670 --> 00:04:40,370
Frances Moulton, shortly after her arrival in England.

00:04:40,370 --> 00:04:43,780
That name may not be without significance.

00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:47,220
You think this Mr. Moulton has some connection with her disappearance?

00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:49,860
I neither affirm nor deny.

00:04:49,860 --> 00:04:52,490
I merely note the possibility.

00:04:52,490 --> 00:04:55,399
Remember, Watson, that in the problem of disappearance,

00:04:55,399 --> 00:05:01,269
one must first determine whether the person has vanished voluntarily or by compulsion.

00:05:01,269 --> 00:05:04,079
That distinction is fundamental.

00:05:04,079 --> 00:05:05,099
..

00:05:05,099 --> 00:05:07,699
He leaned back, clasped his hands behind his head

00:05:07,699 --> 00:05:12,250
and regarded me with that quiet smile which so often accompanied his instruction.

00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:16,610
What do you yourself infer from the facts as presented?

00:05:16,610 --> 00:05:19,069
Well, if I may hazard a guess,

00:05:19,069 --> 00:05:22,539
it seems unlikely that a young lady would abandon her noble husband

00:05:22,539 --> 00:05:25,120
on the very day of marriage without grave reason.

00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:28,439
might she not have been yawed away or forced from the house?

00:05:28,439 --> 00:05:30,680
A reasonable supposition.

00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:35,480
Yet reflect also upon the independence of her character,

00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:38,410
her previous acquaintance with another gentleman,

00:05:38,410 --> 00:05:41,039
and the suddenness of her disappearance.

00:05:41,039 --> 00:05:43,620
If she fled of her own accord,

00:05:43,620 --> 00:05:46,560
those circumstances would harmonize.

00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:52,170
If she were abducted, why should no cry be heard, no trace left?

00:05:52,170 --> 00:05:54,160
True, I had not considered that.

00:05:54,160 --> 00:06:09,160
then again watson never neglect the minor details consider her dress her ornaments her behavior at the breakfast table such trifles properly observed may speak volumes

00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:23,840
as he spoke mrs hudson entered with a card upon a tray holmes took it up glanced at the inscription and passed it to me it bore the name of lord robert walsingham de veris and simon

00:06:23,839 --> 00:06:29,279
Our noble client is at the door. Let us admit him without delay.

00:06:29,279 --> 00:06:37,129
In another moment there entered a tall, aristocratic figure, thin of face, with hop-like features and a certain languid, haughtiness of manner.

00:06:37,129 --> 00:06:41,220
His frock coat was spotlessly cut and a single red rose adorned his buttonhole.

00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:46,769
Yet despite his composure, there lurked upon his countenance a trace of vexation not to be disguised.

00:06:46,769 --> 00:06:52,539
Mr. Holmes, I presume I have come to you because the situation in which I find myself is beyond the capacity of the police.

00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:56,780
As he adds he adds, I cannot endure the indignity of public conjecture.

00:06:56,780 --> 00:07:00,759
My bride, my wife, has disappeared, and I demand that you trace her.

00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:06,020
Tray be seated. Lord St. Simon, this is my friend and colleague, Dr. Watson.

00:07:06,020 --> 00:07:10,040
We are already acquainted with the broad facts of the case through the press,

00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:13,420
but your own account will naturally be more precise.

00:07:13,420 --> 00:07:14,830
Then I shall be brief.

00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:18,040
Yesterday, as all the world knows, I was united to Miss Hattie de Horan,

00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:21,259
daughter of Mr. Istanbul, Francis de Horan of San Francisco.

00:07:21,259 --> 00:07:23,740
Sure, the ceremony passed without incident.

00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:27,079
My bride seemed somewhat agitated, but I ascribed it to natural noseness.

00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:30,659
At the breakfast afterwards she excused herself, and from that moment I have seen her no more.

00:07:30,659 --> 00:07:33,199
The search of the house proved fruitless.

00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:36,659
Later inquiries revealed that she was observed in Hyde Park in company with a gentleman.

00:07:36,659 --> 00:07:38,500
Since then, nothing.

00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,959
This is indeed most remarkable.

00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:43,539
You say she was observed with a gentleman.

00:07:43,539 --> 00:07:45,019
Can you describe him?

00:07:45,019 --> 00:07:47,159
Unfortunately, the description is vague.

00:07:47,159 --> 00:07:49,379
A tall man with a moustache?

00:07:49,379 --> 00:07:51,049
That is all that could be learned.

00:07:51,049 --> 00:08:08,879
and what of your relations with your bride before the wedding did you notice any circumstance which might bear upon this sudden flight none whatever i paid her the usual attentions she accepted them graciously her father was most anxious for the union and i myself was sincerely attached to her

00:08:08,879 --> 00:08:20,579
sincerely attached you say forgive me lord saintst simon if i press a delicate point was the marriage one of affection or of convenience

00:08:20,579 --> 00:08:30,199
with haughte sir i am a nobleman my house is ancient and my purse is light the lady brought wealth i brought position it was a suitable alliance but i did not lack regard for her

